The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Sasken Communication Technologies has posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 6.39 crore in the first quarter ended June 30, a fall of 31 per cent compared with the same period of the previous fiscal. The company has posted a 41 per cent rise in consolidated revenues during the quarter at Rs 128.37 crore. It added 199 employees this quarter, taking the total staff strength to 3,513 as on June 30.

 Tata Elxsi has recently demonstrated its capability to develop mobile TV solutions at the OMA BCAST v.1.0 standards interoperability test camp in Berlin. The camp was organised by by the Broadcast Mobile Convergence Forum. The company showed its middleware support for OMA BCAST service guide profile on the client end.

 S. Kumars Nationwide Ltd has recorded a net profit of Rs 42.66 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 25.02 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Turnover grew 42.8 per cent to Rs 378.85 crore from Rs 265.34 crore a year ago. Operating margin has risen to 20.82 per cent from 20.39 per cent.

 The factory of PT TVS Motor Indonesia was recently inaugurated at the Surya Cipta Estate in Karawang, Indonesia. The factory has been set up on 20 hectares and has the capacity to manufacture 300,000 TVS Neo units every year.

 HCL Infosystems Ltd has launched a six-week campaign called Monsoon Double Dhamaka for its desktop and notebook customers. The campaign, launched in association with Intel Corporation, offers on-the-spot gifts such as Reebok bags, domestic return air tickets and free holiday vouchers with every HCL computer.

 Kotak India Alternate Opportunities Fund, which focuses on real estate and alternate opportunities, has raised an aggregate corpus of over Rs 1,600 crore ($400 million). The corpus has been raised entirely from domestic investors and will be managed by Kotak Mahindra Investments Ltd.

 Titan Nebula has announced a monsoon offer for its customers in the city. Under the offer, customers will get a free Philips DVD player worth Rs 3,499 with every purchase of a Titan Nebula. The offer will be valid till August 5.

 Info Edge (India) Ltd has launched a website, asknaukri.com. The website has been designed to offer information on careers without any charge. The website provides calibrated counselling to work-related queries. 

